Method 1 (CMD / PowerShell):
    - GO TO python.org/downloads click on download and install
    - after installing, open your terminal and type in python
    - it will show the current version of python installed on your windows


Method2 :
    - Open our linux terminal (ubuntu)
    - sudo apt update
    - sudo apt install python3 python3-pip
    - python3 --version



PIP :
    - package manager for Python (just like we have npm for nodejs/js)



